# Support Ticket Structured Data Extraction

## Overview
This project uses an LLM to extract structured JSON data from unstructured customer support tickets.

## Fields Extracted
- issue_category
- urgency (low / medium / high)
- sentiment (positive / negative / neutral)
- one_sentence_summary

## Approach
- Designed a strict system prompt to enforce JSON output
- Used temperature = 0 for deterministic results
- Implemented validation to ensure all fields are present
- Added fallback logic to handle API failures

## Test Cases
- 5 normal tickets with different tones
- 1 confusing ticket with mixed sentiment and unclear urgency

## Confusing Case Insight
- Added rules:
  - Default urgency = medium if unclear
  - Choose dominant sentiment if mixed

## How to Run
1. Set API key as environment variable:
   setx OPENAI_API_KEY "your_key"

2. Run:
   python support_ticket_extractor.py

## Notes
- If API quota is exceeded, fallback logic is used
- Ensures system always returns valid JSON